00:19:02.639 --> 00:19:03.930 align:middle line:90%
So I'd read books about horses.

00:19:03.930 --> 00:19:04.638 align:middle line:90%
>>MONTANA: Right.

00:19:04.638 --> 00:19:06.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it's
such a deep love.

00:19:06.310 --> 00:19:08.290 align:middle line:90%
What is this?

00:19:08.290 --> 00:19:09.840 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: I wish
I knew for sure.

00:19:09.840 --> 00:19:12.830 align:middle line:84%
I know that the horse is
seen as a power animal.

00:19:12.830 --> 00:19:16.240 align:middle line:84%
In the medicine cards, horse
is about power and strength.

00:19:16.240 --> 00:19:19.730 align:middle line:84%
And I think, perhaps if I
wanted to get all psychological,

00:19:19.730 --> 00:19:23.230 align:middle line:84%
it's because we had so little
power that we were attracted

00:19:23.230 --> 00:19:30.590 align:middle line:84%
to these amazingly beautiful,
graceful animals that-- Well,

00:19:30.590 --> 00:19:33.350 align:middle line:84%
horsepower that
powered everything.

00:19:33.350 --> 00:19:34.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:19:34.120 --> 00:19:37.530 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: From the grist
mills to your transportation.

00:19:37.530 --> 00:19:39.530 align:middle line:84%
Everything depended
on horsepower.

00:19:39.530 --> 00:19:42.170 align:middle line:84%
And for the gender
that had no power,

00:19:42.170 --> 00:19:46.740 align:middle line:84%
I think it's kind of natural
that we went in that direction.

00:19:46.740 --> 00:19:48.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that's very
normal for young girls,

00:19:48.740 --> 00:19:50.790 align:middle line:90%
pubescent girls.

00:19:50.790 --> 00:19:52.430 align:middle line:90%
It's an old, old tale.

00:19:52.430 --> 00:19:55.820 align:middle line:84%
And so let's move into
the pubescent years.

00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:58.890 align:middle line:84%
Your sex education
from your mother.

00:19:58.890 --> 00:20:00.476 align:middle line:90%
What was it, one sentence?

00:20:00.476 --> 00:20:02.100 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: Go out
and look at the cows.

00:20:02.100 --> 00:20:03.940 align:middle line:90%
Go out and watch the cows.

00:20:03.940 --> 00:20:08.210 align:middle line:84%
That was my sex education
101, which, of course,

00:20:08.210 --> 00:20:10.951 align:middle line:84%
I went out and watched
the cows, and the heifers

00:20:10.951 --> 00:20:13.200 align:middle line:84%
humped the heifers, and the
steers humped the heifers,

00:20:13.200 --> 00:20:14.900 align:middle line:84%
and the steers
humped the steers.

00:20:14.900 --> 00:20:16.790 align:middle line:84%
And every once and--
the bull and the cows

00:20:16.790 --> 00:20:18.470 align:middle line:84%
actually did very
precious little.

00:20:18.470 --> 00:20:20.860 align:middle line:90%
And I was like really?

00:20:20.860 --> 00:20:23.430 align:middle line:84%
So, as I wrote in the book,
the missionary position

00:20:23.430 --> 00:20:25.885 align:middle line:84%
came as a shock when
I discovered it.

00:20:25.885 --> 00:20:28.800 align:middle line:90%


00:20:28.800 --> 00:20:31.769 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, your mother
obviously was a modest woman.

00:20:31.769 --> 00:20:33.310 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: She was
incredibly modest.

00:20:33.310 --> 00:20:35.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And nor did many
of the women of that era

00:20:35.610 --> 00:20:37.170 align:middle line:90%
have any answers.

00:20:37.170 --> 00:20:39.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, my mother shoved
a little five page

00:20:39.590 --> 00:20:40.257 align:middle line:90%
book in my hand.

00:20:40.257 --> 00:20:42.173 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's what they
did, and walked away.

00:20:42.173 --> 00:20:43.735 align:middle line:84%
And you just learned
to deal with it.

00:20:43.735 --> 00:20:45.620 align:middle line:84%
And you'll figure out
the rest on your own.

00:20:45.620 --> 00:20:48.530 align:middle line:84%
But you did have
over a long period

00:20:48.530 --> 00:20:50.760 align:middle line:84%
of time, kind of a
blossoming of yourself

00:20:50.760 --> 00:20:55.260 align:middle line:84%
with a young man that worked
there with you with the horses.

00:20:55.260 --> 00:20:56.499 align:middle line:90%
>>MONTANA: Oh yeah.

00:20:56.499 --> 00:20:58.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you did kind of
learn through all of that.

00:20:58.790 --> 00:20:59.510 align:middle line:90%
>>MONTANA: Don't we all.

00:20:59.510 --> 00:21:00.930 align:middle line:84%
Haven't we for
thousands of years

00:21:00.930 --> 00:21:02.245 align:middle line:90%
just do what comes naturally.

00:21:02.245 --> 00:21:02.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:21:02.870 --> 00:21:05.790 align:middle line:84%
So you had the boy there
who worked alongside you,

00:21:05.790 --> 00:21:07.400 align:middle line:84%
which we can get
to in a little bit.

00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:10.440 align:middle line:84%
So after you got "the curse,"
and you went on through school,

00:21:10.440 --> 00:21:11.940 align:middle line:84%
and you learned
how to be charming.

00:21:11.940 --> 00:21:13.430 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: And what
a thing to call it.

00:21:13.430 --> 00:21:14.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: "The curse."

00:21:14.180 --> 00:21:14.820 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: What a
thing to call it.

00:21:14.820 --> 00:21:16.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I know, your
mother called it the curse.

00:21:16.040 --> 00:21:17.740 align:middle line:90%
And so did all of them.

00:21:17.740 --> 00:21:20.720 align:middle line:84%
So you go through, and now
you're in this wealthy area,

00:21:20.720 --> 00:21:23.290 align:middle line:84%
and you're in this very
wealthy social scene, which

00:21:23.290 --> 00:21:25.200 align:middle line:90%
is very dysfunctional.

00:21:25.200 --> 00:21:27.450 align:middle line:84%
But you found that
you had power.

00:21:27.450 --> 00:21:28.320 align:middle line:90%
You could flirt.

00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:32.010 align:middle line:84%
You could start using the
feminine wiles with men,

00:21:32.010 --> 00:21:33.850 align:middle line:90%
with young boys.

00:21:33.850 --> 00:21:37.070 align:middle line:84%
And what was that like for you
at that point in your life,

00:21:37.070 --> 00:21:41.780 align:middle line:84%
after having observed the
natural world around you?

00:21:41.780 --> 00:21:44.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: It seemed natural and
unnatural all at the same time.

00:21:44.650 --> 00:21:48.920 align:middle line:84%
It came just like,
whew, out of nowhere.

00:21:48.920 --> 00:21:52.335 align:middle line:84%
I had no sex education, as you
pointed out, like any of us.

00:21:52.335 --> 00:21:53.460 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Nobody did, yeah.

00:21:53.460 --> 00:21:57.790 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: And so it became a
matter of just like something

00:21:57.790 --> 00:22:00.690 align:middle line:90%
that you just do it.

00:22:00.690 --> 00:22:06.680 align:middle line:84%
And I know the attitude hasn't
changed 40, 30 years later.

00:22:06.680 --> 00:22:07.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:22:07.630 --> 00:22:10.205 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: It was
something to do.

00:22:10.205 --> 00:22:12.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you were
proving yourself, too.

00:22:12.080 --> 00:22:13.300 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: And I
was proving myself.

00:22:13.300 --> 00:22:15.258 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You had power
as a feminine creature.

00:22:15.258 --> 00:22:16.781 align:middle line:90%
>>MONTANA: Yes.

00:22:16.781 --> 00:22:17.280 align:middle line:90%
I suppose.

00:22:17.280 --> 00:22:20.200 align:middle line:84%
It was totally
unconscious, Regina.

00:22:20.200 --> 00:22:22.110 align:middle line:84%
I didn't think about
any of this stuff.

00:22:22.110 --> 00:22:24.522 align:middle line:84%
I just went where my
hormones drove me.

00:22:24.522 --> 00:22:25.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: But you are driven.

00:22:25.730 --> 00:22:26.230 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:22:26.230 --> 00:22:28.925 align:middle line:84%
So let's get on down
the road now to college,

00:22:28.925 --> 00:22:30.060 align:middle line:90%
and let's get beyond that.

00:22:30.060 --> 00:22:34.680 align:middle line:84%
Let's get to when you
started in your career, which

00:22:34.680 --> 00:22:36.760 align:middle line:84%
this is where our lives
started paralleling.

00:22:36.760 --> 00:22:40.000 align:middle line:84%
You're talking about a
time when women were not

00:22:40.000 --> 00:22:41.820 align:middle line:84%
in the world of
sports television.

00:22:41.820 --> 00:22:44.450 align:middle line:84%
I was in front of the
camera, my little makeup

00:22:44.450 --> 00:22:46.220 align:middle line:84%
artist and blue
eyeshadow talking

00:22:46.220 --> 00:22:48.400 align:middle line:84%
all about the game
coming up, and you

00:22:48.400 --> 00:22:50.170 align:middle line:90%
were in the truck with the guys.

00:22:50.170 --> 00:22:52.590 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: I was, as a tape
editor, and did slow motion

00:22:52.590 --> 00:22:53.090 align:middle line:90%
replays.

00:22:53.090 --> 00:22:55.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you were the
first at a network level?

00:22:55.500 --> 00:22:58.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: As far as
I'm aware, absolutely.

00:22:58.580 --> 00:23:00.720 align:middle line:84%
The National Association
of Broadcast Engineers

00:23:00.720 --> 00:23:04.810 align:middle line:84%
and Technicians went
on strike in 1977.

00:23:04.810 --> 00:23:06.850 align:middle line:84%
I was called out of
the blue, because I'd

00:23:06.850 --> 00:23:09.660 align:middle line:84%
been working in television
as a director at that point.

00:23:09.660 --> 00:23:12.670 align:middle line:84%
I got a call out of the
blue from some guy in LA

00:23:12.670 --> 00:23:15.420 align:middle line:84%
who was looking to
hire scabs, basically,

00:23:15.420 --> 00:23:18.860 align:middle line:84%
when NABET went
on strike, and did

00:23:18.860 --> 00:23:24.610 align:middle line:84%
I want to run tape at the
1977 Monday Night Football

00:23:24.610 --> 00:23:26.420 align:middle line:90%
opening in Saint Louis.

00:23:26.420 --> 00:23:31.996 align:middle line:84%
And so I said yes, and that was
an answer that changed my life.

00:23:31.996 --> 00:23:36.805 align:middle line:84%
I crossed the picket lines,
hundreds of middle aged men,

00:23:36.805 --> 00:23:38.340 align:middle line:90%
and got to the trucks.

00:23:38.340 --> 00:23:41.734 align:middle line:84%
And 45 other middle
aged men, you

00:23:41.734 --> 00:23:44.150 align:middle line:84%
know, looking like obviously
they know what they're doing,

00:23:44.150 --> 00:23:46.340 align:middle line:90%
and there was me.

00:23:46.340 --> 00:23:48.855 align:middle line:90%
And it was terrifying.

00:23:48.855 --> 00:23:50.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I can imagine.

00:23:50.310 --> 00:23:54.022 align:middle line:84%
It was terrifying being on
my end, and as a token female

00:23:54.022 --> 00:23:54.980 align:middle line:90%
in the world of sports.

00:23:54.980 --> 00:23:57.540 align:middle line:84%
But there were only three of
us in front of the camera.

00:23:57.540 --> 00:23:59.950 align:middle line:84%
You were in a room
full of these men.

00:23:59.950 --> 00:24:01.140 align:middle line:90%
And you were in it.

00:24:01.140 --> 00:24:04.642 align:middle line:84%
It's a very different world,
a more raw world you were in.

00:24:04.642 --> 00:24:06.100 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: It was
a very raw world,

00:24:06.100 --> 00:24:07.780 align:middle line:84%
and I learned to
curse like a sailor,

00:24:07.780 --> 00:24:09.887 align:middle line:84%
and got the hide
of a rhinoceros,

00:24:09.887 --> 00:24:12.220 align:middle line:84%
because if you've ever worked
with any of the ABC sports

00:24:12.220 --> 00:24:15.250 align:middle line:84%
directors you have to have
the hide of a rhinoceros.

00:24:15.250 --> 00:24:18.750 align:middle line:84%
But, you know,
actually it was so up

00:24:18.750 --> 00:24:22.150 align:middle line:84%
my alley, because looking
back there was never

00:24:22.150 --> 00:24:24.380 align:middle line:84%
a time in my life
that I didn't want

00:24:24.380 --> 00:24:26.880 align:middle line:84%
to prove myself
as good as a man.

00:24:26.880 --> 00:24:30.450 align:middle line:84%
It was a-- not even
a subconscious drive.

00:24:30.450 --> 00:24:32.910 align:middle line:84%
I was very aware that
I wanted to go out

00:24:32.910 --> 00:24:36.680 align:middle line:84%
and I wanted to be anything
but like my mother.

00:24:36.680 --> 00:24:38.930 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to prove
myself as good as a guy.

00:24:38.930 --> 00:24:40.200 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to make money.

00:24:40.200 --> 00:24:46.025 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to do it in
however I could most stand out.

00:24:46.025 --> 00:24:48.410 align:middle line:84%
You know, I wasn't
going to be a teacher.

00:24:48.410 --> 00:24:52.050 align:middle line:84%
I was going to end up being a
TV engineer for God's sakes.

00:24:52.050 --> 00:24:53.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:24:53.160 --> 00:24:55.567 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: And I did
really, really well at it.

00:24:55.567 --> 00:24:58.025 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, but when the
time came you had a boyfriend.

00:24:58.025 --> 00:24:59.750 align:middle line:90%
He was in the industry.

00:24:59.750 --> 00:25:02.050 align:middle line:84%
And when it was time to
choose one or the other of you

00:25:02.050 --> 00:25:05.050 align:middle line:90%
for a promotion, it wasn't you.

00:25:05.050 --> 00:25:07.490 align:middle line:90%
>>MONTANA: That's right.

00:25:07.490 --> 00:25:09.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I get that.

00:25:09.140 --> 00:25:12.050 align:middle line:84%
So you were the more
qualified of the two,

00:25:12.050 --> 00:25:15.090 align:middle line:84%
but of course at this time,
that's not going to happen.

00:25:15.090 --> 00:25:17.740 align:middle line:84%
But speak about what happened
when you were passed over,

00:25:17.740 --> 00:25:19.740 align:middle line:84%
the reason you were given
for being passed over.

00:25:19.740 --> 00:25:21.820 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: Oh, this was at
the beginning of my television

00:25:21.820 --> 00:25:22.320 align:middle line:90%
career.

00:25:22.320 --> 00:25:24.100 align:middle line:84%
I was working as
a tape operator.

00:25:24.100 --> 00:25:26.930 align:middle line:84%
I got my boyfriend in
the door about six months

00:25:26.930 --> 00:25:30.350 align:middle line:84%
to eight months after
I got hired at WIS TV.

00:25:30.350 --> 00:25:33.490 align:middle line:84%
And then I was-- a switching
position came open.

00:25:33.490 --> 00:25:35.580 align:middle line:90%
I had been training.

00:25:35.580 --> 00:25:36.980 align:middle line:90%
I was qualified.

00:25:36.980 --> 00:25:41.600 align:middle line:84%
And my-- the Production
Manager took me aside

00:25:41.600 --> 00:25:43.990 align:middle line:84%
and said we've got a
position coming open.

00:25:43.990 --> 00:25:46.740 align:middle line:84%
I know that you're
better qualified,

00:25:46.740 --> 00:25:48.289 align:middle line:90%
but I'm giving it to--

00:25:48.289 --> 00:25:49.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Your boyfriend.

00:25:49.330 --> 00:25:50.413 align:middle line:90%
>>MONTANA: Your boyfriend.

00:25:50.413 --> 00:25:53.570 align:middle line:84%
So he says, because
I know how it is.

00:25:53.570 --> 00:25:56.990 align:middle line:84%
You guys live together, and
it's really hard for men

00:25:56.990 --> 00:25:59.840 align:middle line:90%
to have women surpass them.

00:25:59.840 --> 00:26:02.750 align:middle line:84%
And so it's going to be
easier for your relationship

00:26:02.750 --> 00:26:04.560 align:middle line:90%
if I promote him first.

00:26:04.560 --> 00:26:08.320 align:middle line:84%
And, oh, but thank you for
making that decision for me.

00:26:08.320 --> 00:26:12.750 align:middle line:84%
And I had found that
keeping my lips zipped,

00:26:12.750 --> 00:26:15.060 align:middle line:84%
and not making waves,
and certainly not going

00:26:15.060 --> 00:26:17.140 align:middle line:84%
into emotional
territory had been

00:26:17.140 --> 00:26:19.395 align:middle line:84%
the best way for me
to survive in TV.

00:26:19.395 --> 00:26:20.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:26:20.270 --> 00:26:23.200 align:middle line:84%
>>MONTANA: And so I wasn't
going to jump up and down

00:26:23.200 --> 00:26:26.860 align:middle line:84%
and go, feminism, let
me call my lawyer.

00:26:26.860 --> 00:26:28.490 align:middle line:90%
I just went zip.

00:26:28.490 --> 00:26:32.200 align:middle line:84%
And then I got the
next promotion,

00:26:32.200 --> 00:26:33.557 align:middle line:90%
and then, and then, and then.

00:26:33.557 --> 00:26:34.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I had a very similar--

00:26:34.890 --> 00:26:35.590 align:middle line:90%
>>MONTANA: But it was--

00:26:35.590 --> 00:26:36.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's hard.

00:26:36.060 --> 00:26:36.980 align:middle line:90%
It is horrifying.

00:26:36.980 --> 00:26:39.440 align:middle line:84%
I had a similar
situation as a co-anchor

00:26:39.440 --> 00:26:41.940 align:middle line:90%
in a newscast, nightly newscast.

00:26:41.940 --> 00:26:45.020 align:middle line:84%
And I was called in by
the owner of the station

00:26:45.020 --> 00:26:48.030 align:middle line:84%
to say, could you take
over all the ad-libbing,

00:26:48.030 --> 00:26:50.580 align:middle line:84%
because he didn't have
a natural ability.

00:26:50.580 --> 00:26:53.310 align:middle line:84%
Anything that wasn't scripted
was disastrous at that time.

00:26:53.310 --> 00:26:54.237 align:middle line:90%
It was bad.

00:26:54.237 --> 00:26:56.070 align:middle line:84%
And so they said, would
you please take over

00:26:56.070 --> 00:26:56.889 align:middle line:90%
the control of it.

00:26:56.889 --> 00:26:58.680 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well,
this is kind of weird.

00:26:58.680 --> 00:27:01.890 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that doesn't look
very good for the show.

00:27:01.890 --> 00:27:03.660 align:middle line:84%
But they said, no, we
need you to do this.

00:27:03.660 --> 00:27:07.250 align:middle line:84%
So I'd have to kind of jump in,
and take over all the ad-libs,

00:27:07.250 --> 00:27:09.520 align:middle line:84%
and keep the pace of the
show going, and everything.

00:27:09.520 --> 00:27:12.240 align:middle line:84%
So, as it was time to
renew contracts they said,

00:27:12.240 --> 00:27:14.160 align:middle line:84%
oh, we've just had
a budget cut, and we

00:27:14.160 --> 00:27:16.490 align:middle line:84%
can't have a female
as our sole anchor.

00:27:16.490 --> 00:27:19.030 align:middle line:90%
And they kept him and dumped me.

00:27:19.030 --> 00:27:21.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, these things happened
repeatedly those days

00:27:21.340 --> 00:27:22.070 align:middle line:90%
in television.

00:27:22.070 --> 00:27:23.260 align:middle line:90%
It's just the way it was.

00:27:23.260 --> 00:27:25.360 align:middle line:90%
And I'm not litigious.

00:27:25.360 --> 00:27:27.270 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't going to
go jump up and down.

00:27:27.270 --> 00:27:28.070 align:middle line:90%
Keep it zipped.

00:27:28.070 --> 00:27:29.330 align:middle line:90%
Move on down the road.

00:27:29.330 --> 00:27:31.170 align:middle line:90%
That's what you do.

00:27:31.170 --> 00:27:35.340 align:middle line:84%
And that programming
in and of itself, that

00:27:35.340 --> 00:27:37.509 align:middle line:90%
still lives inside.

00:27:37.509 --> 00:27:38.300 align:middle line:90%
>>MONTANA: It does.

00:27:38.300 --> 00:27:40.360 align:middle line:10%
